headline: How Should Investors View Packaging Corp After Latest Earnings and Guidance Disappointment in 2025?
summary: If you find yourself debating what to do about Packaging Corporation of America right now, you are definitely not alone. The stock has been a bit of a head-scratcher for investors lately, dipping about 1.7% over the past week, and down 1.0% in the past month. Zoom out a bit, though, and the picture gets more interesting. Year-to-date, shares have trimmed off 6.9%, and over the past year, the stock is off 3.1%.
